I have a few main concerns with wearable tech, and the SmartWatch2 seems to address them all;
 Battery life; The SW2 needs charging about as often as my current &lsquo;phone (a Galaxy S4), so putting them both on charge at the same time isn&rsquo;t difficult to remember.

One phrase from last nights Amazon.com Kindle launch makes me think they&rsquo;re going to take over the #Android tablet space and have big consumer support;
&ldquo;&hellip;people don&rsquo;t want gadgets anymore. They want services that improve over time. They want services that improve every day, every week, and every month.&rdquo;
This has been true for a long time. Consumers buy devices from washing machines to TVs because they want it to do something, not because it has the lastest bit of technology from the manufacturer.

